# Postgres & Drizzle (`packages/db`)

## Schema

- Use `timestamptz` for timestamps in SQL migrations.
- Foreign keys with explicit `ON DELETE` behavior.
- Prefer `text` org IDs and UUID run IDs consistent with existing tables.

## Migrations

- Add numbered files under `packages/db/migrations/` (`0007_*.sql`) — do not edit shipped migrations in place.
- Run `pnpm migrate` locally when testing `TRACE_STORE=postgres`.
- Mount new migrations in `docker-compose.yml` initdb sequence when adding tables.

## Queries (Drizzle)

- Use Drizzle builders — never string-interpolate SQL with user input.
- Select explicit columns for hot paths; avoid unbounded lists (audit export uses caps).
- Index FK columns on new tables.

## agentd data rules

- `run_events` stays append-only.
- Secrets: `project_secrets` encrypted at rest; never write secret values to `run_events`.
- Org-scoped queries must filter by `orgId` from auth context.

## Forbidden

- `TRUNCATE` / destructive ops in app code paths.
- Plaintext secrets in migrations or seed data committed to git.
